-- India's NSE index falls 0.4 pct, retreats from record high
-- By Indulal PM
-- Tue Mar 11, 2014 06:14AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, March 11 (Reuters) - India's NSE index provisionally fell, retreating from a record high hit earlier in the day, as investors booked profits in some recent outperformers such as Reliance Industries ahead of key inflation data.

Reliance Industries Ltd <RELI.NS> provisionally fell 1.3 percent after surging 9.7 percent over the previous three sessions, while HDFC Bank Ltd <HDBK.NS> lost 0.97 percent after jumping 9.8 percent over the same period.  The NSE <.NSEI> provisionally fell 0.4 percent to end at 6,511.90, below a record high of 6,562.85 hit earlier in the day and snapping a five-day winning streak.